    <title>Combined summary - Request for a new BIP number (and discussion): Improved HD wallet generation.</title>
    <updated>2023-06-09T17:37:51.376386+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/bitcoin-dev/2015-February/007520.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>Jona has proposed a new generation methodology for HD wallets based on a modified version of BIP32 that requires accidental disclosure of two private keys to compute the master private key. Jona is open to criticism and help with making the BIP more secure, and he has shared a link to his proposal and PGP public key block.In an email exchange with Pavol Rusnak, Jona was advised that his proposal was missing important sections, namely Abstract and Motivation. Jona later thanked Pavol for his feedback. Bob expressed concerns about the security of the proposed modification, but the proposer explained that as long as the keys are generated within their specifications, it is not possible to derive the associated extended private key to the ancestor extended public key.Jona also updated an algorithm to include b in the derivation of a and vice versa. He plans to write out how to compromise the parent private node with two child private nodes and the parent public node. This highlights Jona's dedication to improving the security of HD wallets and his willingness to collaborate with others to achieve this goal.Overall, this context underscores the importance of digital security in today's interconnected world. With the increasing use of online transactions and sensitive information being stored digitally, it is crucial to develop secure methods of storing and transmitting data. The work of individuals like Jona and the feedback provided by experts like Pavol Rusnak demonstrate the ongoing effort to improve digital security.</summary>
